  "prompt": "How can evaporated milk be substituted for condensed milk?",
  "response": "Evaporated milk and condensed milk are different products, primarily due to the addition of sugar in condensed milk, which gives it a thick, sweet flavor. If you need to substitute evaporated milk for condensed milk, here\u2019s a method to create a substitute:\n\n### Substitute for 1 cup of Condensed Milk:\n\n1. **Ingredients:**\n   - 1 cup of evaporated milk\n   - 1 cup of granulated sugar\n\n2. **Instructions:**\n   - In a saucepan, combine the evaporated milk and granulated sugar.\n   - Heat the mixture over medium heat, stirring continuously until the sugar completely dissolves. Do not allow it to boil.\n   - Once the sugar is dissolved, remove it from heat and let it cool. The mixture will thicken slightly as it cools.\n\n### Tips:\n- If you're looking for a quick usage without cooking, you can use 1 cup of evaporated milk combined with about 1/2 to 1 cup of sugar (depending on how sweet you want it) and mix it well.\n- The substituted mixture may have a slightly different flavor or consistency than store-bought sweetened condensed milk but can work well in recipes.\n- Keep in mind this method will add sweetness and change the overall flavor profile of your dish. Adjust sugar levels if your recipe has additional sweet components.\n\nThis homemade substitute can typically be used in recipes calling for condensed milk, especially in baking or dessert dishes.",
